This paper is about a neural network model for text summarization, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses reinforcement learning (RL) to train the model, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is trained using policy gradients, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of parallel decoding, which is a technique commonly used in neural network models for natural language generation (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on the DUC-2002 dataset, which is a dataset commonly used for text summarization research (cs.IR).
